Using exwm with emacs-in-emacs I sometimes make a mistake and start a shell-process going that I need to stop. However, C-c is grabbed by my parent exwm session and so doesn&rsquo;t send anything to my shell. How can I do this manually?
Answer C-c C-c is short for comint-interrupt-subjob
